This article is a letter from President Barack Obama to the Chairmen and Ranking Members of the House Committee on Ways and Means and the Senate Committee on Finance. The letter is regarding Bolivia and Ecuador and their eligibility for the Andean Trade Preference Act (ATPA). President Obama states that he is transmitting a report that outlines his determinations based on a review of Bolivia and Ecuador's performance with respect to the ATPA's eligibility criteria. The report also includes a summary of the developments and concerns in four key areas outlined in the ATPA.